title: get column label from meta data object should return recognizable strings
description: When calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() on a meta data object before data extraction, the labels returned are null. However, after data extraction, the labels returned are recognizable strings.
OB: Before data extraction, the labels returned by IMetaData.getColumnLabel() are null.
EB: After data extraction, calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() should return recognizable strings for the column labels.
SR:
To reproduce the issue, perform the following steps:
1. Create a meta data object.
2. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() on the meta data object before data extraction.
3. Verify that the returned labels are null.
4. Extract data.
5. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() on the meta data object after data extraction.
6. Verify that the returned labels are recognizable strings for the column labels.
